data.name: digest
data.description: The digest algorithm can be: 'MD5', 'SHA1', 'SHA256' or 'SHA512'
This endpoint generates a new challenge. The digest algorithm can be: 'MD5', 'SHA1', 'SHA256' or 'SHA512'
data.name: Generate Challenge

data.description: This endpoint validates a Certificate chain and performs an OCSP/CRL check. The first certificate must be the leaf certificate, followed by one or more intermediate certificates. The last certificate in the chain must be the root issuer. The leaf certificate should start with order '0'. Certificates should be base64 encoded strings.
data.name: Validate Certificate Chain

data.description: This endpoint validates signatures. The digest algorithm can be: 'MD5', 'SHA1', 'SHA256' or 'SHA512'. Default SHA1 is used.
data.name: Validate Signature by Certificate

data.description: This endpoint validates a signed challenge (for example 'strong authentication'). The challenge must be generated with a GET request on '/challenge'.
data.name: Validate Signed Challenge

description: The API provides endpoints to generate challenges, validate signature and certificate chains (PKI).
name: v1
